content:
Strong women till the fields, yet crops come not as well as before; 
Lads from around here are well known for their bravery, but hate to be driven like dogs or chickens;
Only because you kindly ask me do I dare give vent to grievances;
Now the year is ending, yet the men from the western frontier still have not returned; the government demands immediate payment of taxes, but how can we pay when so little has been produced? Now, we peasants have learnt one thing: To have a son is not so good as having a daughter
A daughter can marry a neighbor and still be near us, while a son will be taken away to die in the grass in some wild place"

The words 'Sometimes, the lord's orders may not be received' are meant for the ears of kings and lords, not for battle commanders

If a commander on the front lines wants to be able to 'not receive' his lord's commands, first he must be committed to sacrificing himself.
